   - Ensure that the system can handle multiple users and their preferences.\n\n5. **Document the Code:**\n   - Add comments and docstrings to explain the purpose and functionality of the code.\n   - Write a README file to provide an overview of the project and instructions for setting up and running the system.\n\nHere is a brief example of what the initial `solution.py` might look like:\n\n```python\n# solution.py\n# CollaborativeTravelPlanner System\n# This system facilitates the planning of group travel itineraries by integrating\n# individual preferences and coordinating among multiple users.\n\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n# In-memory storage for user preferences\nuser_preferences = defaultdict(list)\n\ndef aggregate_preferences():\n    """Aggregates user preferences to generate a cohesive itinerary."""\n    # Simple aggregation logic (this would be more complex in a real-world scenario)\n    aggregated_preferences = {}\n    for user, preferences in user_preferences.items():\n        for preference in preferences:\n            if preference not in aggregated_preferences:\n                aggregated_preferences[preference] = 0\n            aggregated_preferences[preference] += 1\n    return aggregated_preferences\n\ndef generate_itinerary(aggregated_preferences):\n    """Generates a cohesive itinerary based on aggregated preferences."""\n    # Simple itinerary generation logic (this would be more complex in a real-world scenario)\n    itinerary = sorted(aggregated_preferences.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    return itinerary\n\n@app.route(\'/add_preferences\', methods=[\'POST\'])\ndef add_preferences():\n    """Endpoint to add user preferences."""\n    data = request.json\n    user_id = data.get(\'user_id\')\n    preferences = data.get(\'preferences\', [])\n    user_preferences[user_id].extend(preferences)\n    return jsonify({"message": "Preferences added successfully"}), 200\n\n@app.route(\'/generate_itinerary\', methods=[\'GET\'])\ndef generate_itinerary_endpoint():\n    """Endpoint to generate a cohesive itinerary."""\n    aggregated_preferences = aggregate_preferences()\n    itinerary = generate_itinerary(aggregated_preferences)\n    return jsonify({"itinerary": itinerary}), 200\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    app.run(debug=True)\n```\n\n### Additional Steps:\n\n1. **Create a README File:**\n   - Provide an overview of the project.\n   - Include instructions for setting up and running the system.\n   - Mention any dependencies and how to install them.\n\n2. **Write Unit Tests:**\n   - Create a `tests` directory and add test files.\n   - Write basic unit tests to verify the functionality of the endpoints and core logic.\n\n3. **Organize the Project:**\n   - If the project grows, consider organizing it into modules and packages.\n   - For example, you might have `models`, `views`, `utils`, and `tests` directories.\n\n### Example README File:\n\n```markdown\n# CollaborativeTravelPlanner\n\n## Overview\nCollaborativeTravelPlanner is a distributed system that facilitates the planning of group travel itineraries by integrating individual preferences and coordinating among multiple users. The system generates a cohesive itinerary that maximizes group satisfaction while ensuring logistical feasibility.\n\n## Setup\n1. **Install Dependencies:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install Flask\n   ```\n\n2. **Run the Application:**\n   ```bash\n   python solution.py\n   ```\n\n## Endpoints\n- **Add Preferences:**\n  - **Endpoint:** `/add_preferences`\n  - **Method:** `POST`\n  - **Request Body:**\n    ```json\n    {\n      "user_id": "user1",\n      "preferences": ["Paris", "Eiffel Tower", "Louvre Museum"]\n    }\n    ```\n\n- **Generate Itinerary:**\n  - **Endpoint:** `/generate_itinerary`\n  - **Method:** `GET`\n  - **Response:**\n    ```json\n    {\n      "itinerary": [\n        ["Eiffel Tower", 2],\n        ["Louvre Museum", 2],\n        ["Par